solution:
Instead of plugging in $x=7$ into $f(x)$ and solving, we can use the Remainder Theorem to avoid complicated arithmetic. We know that $f(7)$ will be the remainder when $f(x)$ is divided by $x-7$. So we have:

\[
\begin{array}{c|ccccc}
